<chapter id="faq">
<title>Frequently Asked Questions</title>
<qandaset>

<qandaentry>
<question>
<para>
Can I redirect ships once they have left a planet?
</para>
</question>
<answer>
<para>
No, once ships leave a planet, they cannot be stopped or redirected.
</para>
</answer>
</qandaentry>

<qandaentry>
<question>
<para>
Do the different colors and shapes of planets mean anything?
</para>
</question>
<answer>
<para>
No, they are random.
</para>
</answer>
</qandaentry>

<qandaentry>
<question>
<para>
How can I know where my ships are?
</para>
</question>
<answer>
<para>
Click <guibutton>Show Standings</guibutton>. It will give you information about fleets currently in flight.
</para>
</answer>
</qandaentry>

<qandaentry>
<question>
<para>
I have lost all my planets, but I am still in the game, why?
</para>
</question>
<answer>
<para>
You have not lost the game until you have lost all your ships.
</para>
</answer>
</qandaentry>

<qandaentry>
<question>
<para>
I am running out of turns, what can I do?
</para>
</question>
<answer>
<para>
You can continue playing. When you are at the last turn, you will be prompted to add more.
</para>
</answer>
</qandaentry>

<qandaentry>
<question>
<para>
Can I store ships on a planet for later use?
</para>
</question>
<answer>
<para>
Yes, you should however store them on multiple planets to be able to send them to nearby planets.
</para>
</answer>
</qandaentry>

<qandaentry>
<question>
<para>
I have sent out all the ships on a planet, but when I move my mouse over the planet, it shows the ships still in place, why?
</para>
</question>
<answer>
<para>
The number of ships on a planet is updated when a turn is ended.
</para>
</answer>
</qandaentry>

<qandaentry>
<question>
<para>
Is it possible to change the theme?
</para>
</question>
<answer>
<para>
No, that is not possible at the moment.
</para>
</answer>
</qandaentry>

</qandaset>
